'\" t
.TH "ACTON\-WRAPPER" "1"
.nh
.ad l
.ss \n[.ss] 0
.SH "NAME"
acton\-wrapper \[em] Generate Tolk or TypeScript wrappers for a contract
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBacton wrapper\fR [\fIoptions\fR] \fIcontract\-id\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generate a wrapper for the contract identified by \fB_contract\-id_\fR from
\fBActon.toml\fR\&.
.sp
Wrapper generation uses the ABI emitted by the Tolk compiler. In practice, the
contract header is the source of truth for typed storage accessors, incoming
message helpers, and generated get\-method bindings.
.sp
The command can also generate a stub test file or emit a TypeScript wrapper for
frontend and tooling integrations.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.SS "Wrapper Options"
.sp
\fIcontract\-id\fR
.RS 4
Contract ID from \fBActon.toml\fR to generate the wrapper for.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Write the generated wrapper to an exact path.
.sp
Conflicts with \fB\-\-output\-dir\fR\&.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-output\-dir\fR \fIdir\fR
.RS 4
Write the generated wrapper to a directory and let Acton choose the file name.
.sp
Conflicts with \fB\-\-output\fR\&.
.RE
.SS "Test Stub Options"
.sp
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-test\fR
.RS 4
Generate a stub test file together with the wrapper.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-test\-output\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Write the generated test file to an exact path.
.sp
Requires \fB\-\-test\fR\&.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-test\-output\-dir\fR \fIdir\fR
.RS 4
Write the generated test file to a directory and let Acton choose the file
name.
.sp
Requires \fB\-\-test\fR and conflicts with \fB\-\-test\-output\fR\&.
.RE
.SS "TypeScript Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-ts\fR
.RS 4
Generate a TypeScript wrapper through \fBgen\-typescript\-from\-tolk\fR\&.
.sp
Conflicts with test stub generation.
.RE
.SS "Display Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-color\fR \fIwhen\fR
.RS 4
Control when to use colored output.
.sp
Possible values: \fBauto\fR, \fBalways\fR, \fBnever\fR
.RE
.SS "Project Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-manifest\-path\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Path to the \fBActon.toml\fR file to use for this invocation.
.sp
Use this when running the command outside the project directory or when the
manifest lives at a non\-default location.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-project\-root\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Path to the project root to use for configuration discovery and relative
defaults.
.sp
This conflicts with \fB\-\-manifest\-path\fR\&.
.RE
.SH "ABI REQUIREMENTS"
Wrapper generation depends on the contract ABI exposed by the Tolk compiler.
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fBstorage: ...\fR enables typed storage helpers such as \fBfromStorage\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fBincomingMessages: ...\fR enables \fBsend{Message}\fR helpers
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'declared get methods are emitted as wrapper methods
.RE
.sp
If \fBincomingMessages\fR is missing, message\-sending helpers are not generated. If
\fBstorage\fR is missing, storage helpers fall back to an untyped initializer.
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
Project\-wide defaults can be configured in \fBActon.toml\fR:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
[wrappers.tolk]
output\-dir = "tests/wrappers"
generate\-test = true
test\-output\-dir = "tests"

[wrappers.typescript]
output\-dir = "wrappers"
.fi
.RE
.sp
CLI flags override config values for the current invocation.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 1.\h'+01'Generate the default Tolk wrapper:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton wrapper counter
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 2.\h'+01'Generate a wrapper and stub test:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton wrapper counter \-\-test
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 3.\h'+01'Generate a TypeScript wrapper:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton wrapper counter \-\-ts
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 4.\h'+01'Generate into custom locations:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton wrapper counter \-\-output\-dir tests/generated
acton wrapper counter \-\-test \-\-test\-output\-dir tests/generated
acton wrapper counter \-\-ts \-\-output\-dir wrappers
.fi
.RE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fBacton help build\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fBacton help test\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fIGenerating wrappers guide\fR <https://ton\-blockchain.github.io/acton/docs/test\-runner/generating\-wrappers>
.RE
